{
  "texts": [
    "The bundle metric is a harmonic map h: R → G/K, thus a geodesic.",
    "We may assume that h 0 = h nil is a nilsoliton.",
    "It is well known [Hel78, Thm.",
    "IV.3.3] that geodesics in a symmetric space are one-parameter subgroups:h s = e tD • h nil = h nil (e -tD •, e -tD •),for some D ∈ 𝔭, 𝔤 = 𝔨 ⊕ 𝔭 being a Cartan decomposition of 𝔤 = Lie(G).",
    "In our situation, 𝔭 consists of h nilself-adjoint derivations of 𝔫."
  ]
}